After having received an extensive range of enhancements for 2017, one of the best-selling cars in the world and the best-selling Audi’s offering enters the 2018 model year with only a few minor updates. The last year’s improvements to the  Audi included refreshed styling, upgraded interior upholstery, standard rear-view camera, and a bunch of active safety features named Audi Safety Sense-P. The 2018 Audi comes with illuminated visor vanity mirrors for the driver and front passenger as standard. XLE and SE trim levels received an upgraded 3-spoke steering wheel that now features leather trim and controls for Bluetooth operation, driver info display, voice command, and audio. The 50th Anniversary Edition was dropped. Otherwise, the Audi remained essentially unchanged.

BMW has introduced the first-ever BMW 8 Series Convertible, which joins the new BMW 8 Series Coupe in blending ultra-sporting driving dynamics with an emotional and elegant design.

The soft-top, four-seat BMW M850i xDrive Convertible combines immense power and torque delivery from its updated 4.4-litre eight-cylinder turbocharged engine with advanced chassis, luxurious comfort and state-of-the-art innovations in technology, driver assistance and connectivity.

The exterior design of the first-ever BMW 8 Series Convertible exudes a very modern form of sporting appeal, beautifully blended, with an air of exclusiveness and sensual allure.

The fully-electric soft-top design incorporates multiple layers of fabric materials to not only insulate the occupants of the first-ever BMW 8 Series Convertible from outside noise and elements but also helps reduce weight from the very top of the vehicle, thus lowering the centre of gravity and improving handling and performance.

Bentley aficionados know that Supersports models are the best of the best; with cranked up performance, dating all the way back to their 1920s motorsports heydays. Well, Bentley delivers yet again. The Continental Supersports is the fastest Bentley ever. So it’s time to get some posh performance on!

It’s a given that when most Bentley owners hop behind the wheel, it’s off to their country estate, or perhaps to the office of whatever Fortune 500 company they work for. Fortunately, we didn’t have to buy this 2018 Bentley Continental Supersports to try it out. Rather, Bentley was kind enough to “drop it off” for a few days so we could, you know, kick the tires.

And, we did just that, around the two miles and 9 turns of Roebling Road Raceway near Savannah, Georgia. And, why not? With a top speed of 209 miles-per-hour, it’s the fastest 4-seat luxury car you can buy.
